.TH AXT-CTXPACK 1
.SH NAME
axt-ctxpack \- search local files for multiple named regex patterns
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-ctxpack
--pattern NAME=REGEX [--pattern NAME=REGEX]... [ROOT...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-ctxpack
performs bounded multi-pattern context search over local UTF-8 text files.
Directory traversal is gitignore-aware by default. Supported source files are
classified with embedded tree-sitter parsers; unsupported files fall back to
line heuristics.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --pattern NAME=REGEX
Named regex to search for. Repeatable and required.
.TP
.B --files GLOB
Include glob. Repeatable.
.TP
.B --include GLOB
Include glob. Repeatable.
.TP
.B --context N
Context lines around each match. Default: 0.
.TP
.B --hidden
Include hidden files.
.TP
.B --no-ignore
Disable ignore and gitignore filters.
.TP
.B --json, --agent
Select output mode.
.TP
.B --limit N, --max-bytes BYTES, --strict
Control output truncation.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, 2 for invalid input, 3 for missing paths, 4 for permission errors, 6 for strict truncation, and 8 for filesystem or output errors.
.SH SEE ALSO
axt-outline(1)
